===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|welth}}, {{m|enm|welthe}}, {{m|enm|weolthe||happiness, prosperity}}, from {{inh|en|ang|*welþ}}, {{m|ang|*weleþu}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*waliþō|t=wealth}}.
Alternatively, possibly an alteration (due to similar words in {{m|enm|-th}}: compare {{m|enm|helth|t=health}}, {{m|enm|derth|t=dearth}}) of {{m|enm|wele|t=wealth, well-being, weal}}, from {{inh|en|ang|wela|t=wealth, prosperity}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*walô|t=well-being, prosperity}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*wel-|t=good, best}}; equivalent to {{suffix|en|weal|th}}. Cognate with {{cog|nl|weelde|t=wealth}}, {{cog|nds|weelde|t=wealth}}, {{cog|goh|welida}}, {{m|goh|welitha|t=wealth}}. Related also to {{cog|de|Wohl|t=welfare, well-being, weal}}, {{cog|da|vel|t=weal, welfare}}, {{cog|sv|väl|t=well-being, weal}}. More at {{l|en|weal}}, {{l|en|well}}.

